gurmukhi: mhwdIn kyqy piRQI mwNJ hUey ]smY AwpnI AwpnI AMq mUey ]27]
transliteration: Mahaadoon Kete Prithoo Maanjh Hooe|| Samai Aapanoo Aapanoo Ant Moond||27||
translation: Many Muhammads had been on the earth. They were born and then died in their own times. 27.

gurmukhi: ijqy AaulIAw AMbIAw hoie bIqy ]iqiqE kwl jIqw n qy kwl jIqy ]
transliteration: Jite Aulooaa Anbooaa Hoe Boote|| Titio Kaal Jeetaa N Ate Kaal Jeete||
translation: All the Prophets and saints of the past were conquered by Death (KAL), but none could conquer it (him).

gurmukhi: ijqy rwm sy kiRsn huie ibsn Awey ]iqiqE kwl KwipE n qy kwl Gwey ]28]
transliteration: Jite Raam Se Krisan Hue Bisan Aae|| Titio Kaal Khaapio N Ate Kaal Ghaae||28||
translation: All the incarnations of Vishnu like Rama and Krishan were destroyed by KAL, but they could not destroy him. 28.

gurmukhi: ijqy ieMdR sy cMdR sy hoq Awey ]iqiqE kwl Kwpw n qy kwl Gwey ]
transliteration: Jite Indra Se Channdra Se Hot Aae|| Titio Kaal Khaapaa Na Te Kaal Ghaae||
translation: All the indras and Chandras (moons) who came into being were destroyed by KAL, but they could not destroy him.

gurmukhi: ijqy AOlIAw AMbIAw gOs hÍYhYN ]sBY kwl ky AMq dwVw qlY hYN ]29]
transliteration: Jite Aulooaa Anbooaa Gaddd Hvaihain|| Sabhai Kaal Ke Ant Daadaa Talai Hain||29||
translation: All those Prophets, saints and hermits, who came into being, were all ultimately crushed under the grinder tooth of KAL.29.

gurmukhi: ijqy mwnDwqwid rwjw suhwey ]sBY bwND kY kwl jylY clwey ]
transliteration: Jite Maandhaataadh Raajaa Suhaae|| Sabhai Baandh Kai Kaal Jelai Chadhaae||
translation: All the glorious kings like Mandhata were all bound down and thrown in the noose of KAL.

gurmukhi: ijnY nwm qw ko aucwro aubwry ]ibnw swm qw kI lKy kot mwry ]30]
transliteration: Jinai Naam Taa Ko Ouchdaro Oubhare|| Binaa Saam Taa Koo Lakhe Kot Mdare||30||
translation: Those who have remembered the Name of the Lord, have been saved, without coming under His refuge, millions are considered as having been killed by KAL.30.
The sword of KAL glistens, which is Non-elemental and terrible.
While moving, his anklets rattle and the small bells jingle.31.
He hath four winsome arms and on his head, his long hair have been bound in a lovely knot.

transliteration: Gadaa Paas Sohan|| Jamannd Maan Mohan||32||
translation: The mace with him appears splendid, which fascinate the honour of Yama.32.

transliteration: Soubhan Joobh Juaalan|| Su Daadhaa Karaalan||
translation: His tongue red like fire seems magnificent and his grinder teeth are very frightening.

transliteration: Badoo Banb Sankhan|| Outhe Naad Bankhan||33||
translation: His conches and drums resound like the thundering sound of the sea. 33.
